sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0097_1777779532.log:2193:docs/startup-wizard.md:145:- The observer path now prefers a dedicated local Ollama queue on `127.0.0.1:11435` through `cypherclaw-observer-ollama.service`, with the shared `11434` queue as fallback. If both are saturated, `observer_vision.py` still stays readable instead of surfacing the raw HTTP error: it emits a short local fallback description, records `vision_backend` / `vision_error` in `/tmp/observer_state.json`, and waits before retrying the slow multimodal call.
