CHANGELOG.md:103:- Added depth-2 artist-identity end-to-end test coverage (frac-0059): `tests/test_artist_identity.py` now ships a `TestArtistIdentityEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public artist-identity surface (`select_mode`, `apply_mode_to_commission`, `next_tonal_choice`, `MODES`, `MODES_BY_NAME`, `HOME_TONAL_MAP`, `VOICE_ROLES`, `SIGNATURE_VOICES`) through looped, table-driven end-to-end methods. The new tests sweep every `ArtistMode` for required commission metadata keys, tempo-band membership across many seeds, voice-count propagation, silence/restraint/harmony field propagation, sampler-density propagation, voice/groove/modal CSV serialization, the `mode_avoid_attention_pullers` string contract, deterministic application across non-zero seeds, input-dict immutability, JSON round-trip safety, and preservation of pre-existing commission keys; verify the entire `HOME_TONAL_MAP` (only `B` is home, `D` and `F#` are the unique distance-1 neighbors, every distance is a non-negative int); walk the documented `select_mode` priority matrix including the inclusive 0.6 STORM threshold, screen-active gating that requires `presence='present'`, equivalent evening/night routing, and a full presence/time/severity/screen sweep that always returns a known mode; sweep `next_tonal_choice` across many seeds for every mode confirming roots stay in `HOME_TONAL_MAP` and scales stay in `mode.preferred_modes`, determinism per (mode, seed), and that modulation-willingness correlates with venturing (SOLITARY <= COMPANION <= STORM); and run the end-to-end `select -> apply -> choose` pipeline across a presence/time/screen matrix with JSON-safe payloads. `tests/test_artist_identity_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing artist-identity assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
