CHANGELOG.md:113:- Added depth-2 pytest collection gate reports (frac-0054): `tests/conftest.py` now exposes a frozen `CollectionGateDecision` dataclass plus `collection_gate_decisions`, `apply_collection_gate_decisions`, and `summarize_collection_gate_decisions` so tests and diagnostics can inspect live/host-specific marker gates with enabled state, skip reason, matched count, skipped count, and JSON-safe totals. Existing `--run-live-modal`, `--run-live-replicate`, `live_modal`, `live_replicate`, and `cypherclaw_e2e` behavior is preserved: Modal/Replicate live tests skip by default unless opted in, and CypherClaw e2e skips on CI. `tests/test_conftest_depth.py` pins hook registration, default and CI gate behavior, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:115:- Added depth-2 test_genai smoke probe (frac-0053): root-level `test_genai.py` is now a typed module exposing a frozen `GenAIProbeResult` dataclass plus `create_genai_client`, `list_model_names`, `probe_genai_client`, `summarize_probe_result`, `format_probe_lines`, and `main` so callers, tests, and operator dashboards can drive `probe → summarize → render → main` without re-implementing the conditional script logic. The success path returns a populated result with the sampled model names; any raised `Exception` is folded into an `ok=False` result with the stringified error and zero models. `summarize_probe_result` is JSON-safe (`sampled_models` rendered as a list); `format_probe_lines` preserves the original CLI output format byte-for-byte ("Successfully created client without explicit API key." header plus per-model lines on success, single "Error: <error>" line on failure); `main()` runs the probe and prints each line, returning exit code 0 to match the original `python test_genai.py` smoke behavior. `tests/test_test_genai_depth.py` pins the new probe surface, client construction (explicit key + default-auth env), limit-respecting model sampling, success/error result paths, JSON-safe summary, canonical CLI line rendering, end-to-end main, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` and the startup identity anchors remain green.
