docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:180:The integrity checker runs as part of the verify phase and treats format violations identically to semantic failures. A task that adds correct code without a docstring gets the same "ESCALATED" verdict as a task that produces broken code.
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:205:exec sdp-cli orchestrate --start-phase development --end-phase development
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:208:`orchestrate` is a single-run command that exits when it finishes a phase. For an unattended 24/7 runner, this is the wrong primitive — it should be `run` (which loops until interrupted) or `run --force` (which also bypasses the breaker).
