sdp/verification/t-015@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:62:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-26T00:47:41.123Z","tool_name":"run_shell_command","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777164461123_0","parameters":{"description":"Writing the verification report.","command":"cat <<EOF > sdp/verification/t-015@20260425t183959zd-verify.md\n# Verification Report — T-015 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-015_20260425T183959Zd_1777164411.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-26\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** \n- .github/workflows/detector-smoke.yml\n- tests/fixtures/audio/README.md\n- tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py\n- my-claw/tools/sample_capture_daemon.py\n\n## Correctness\nThe CI job was correctly added to \\`.github/workflows/detector-smoke.yml\\` and is configured to run on every push and pull request. It specifically targets the smoke tests in \\`tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py\\` using the \\`-k \"fixture or smoke\"\\` selector. The job includes a 30-second timeout guard as required.\n\n## Completeness\nThe documentation in \\`tests/fixtures/audio/README.md\\` is comprehensive, covering the purpose of the fixtures, how to regenerate them using \\`generate.py\\`, and when regeneration is necessary. The smoke tests cover all detector branches (footsteps, music, dogs, transient_cluster) and baselines (silence, dishwasher).\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation follows established patterns. The use of canned WAV fixtures for CI-level smoke testing without requiring live audio or JACK dependencies is consistent with the project's testing strategy for the sample-capture subsystem.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities or leaked secrets were found. The use of deterministic RNG seeds for fixture generation ensures reproducibility without introducing security risks.\n\n## Quality\nThe smoke tests are extremely fast (runtime ~0.2s for the selected tests), well under the 30s limit. The hardening requirement to invoke \\`bootstrap_identity()\\` at startup is addressed in \\`my-