# Changelog

## Unreleased

- Added depth-2 render-events end-to-end test coverage (frac-0104): `tests/test_render_events.py` now includes `RenderEventsEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `src/cypherclaw/render/events.py` public surface through one realistic two-event lifecycle: a non-trivial `SectionEnvelope` is sampled and per-parameter `value_at(...)` agrees with the `SectionEnvelopeSample` for every `SECTION_ENVELOPE_PARAMETERS` channel, a custom `PerformanceIntent` round-trips its declared fields, two `Event` instances (phrase-start `IntentTag.BUILD` and phrase-end / cadential `IntentTag.SETTLE`) populate the full `Event` field surface, `lock_score_fields()` freezes every member of `Event.SCORE_LEVEL_FIELDS` while leaving sensor / timing / `rule_stack` mutable, both events round-trip through `to_json_dict()`/`from_json_dict()`, `to_json()`/`from_json()`, and `to_osc_bundle()`/`from_osc_bundle()` with structural equality and preserved `seed_path` tuples, and a combined diagnostic of `IntentTag` membership, `VALID_ARC_SHAPES`, `SECTION_ENVELOPE_PARAMETERS`, the sampled envelope values, the `PerformanceIntent` snapshot, and both event JSON dicts round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_render_events_depth.py` pins the render-events test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the events module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4631 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

- Added depth-2 render-antipattern end-to-end test coverage (frac-0103): `tests/test_render_antipatterns.py` now includes `RenderAntipatternsEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/antipatterns.py` public surface through one mixed rendered-piece diagnostic (`detect_antipatterns(...)`, `failing_antipatterns(...)`, warning vs. blocking severity grouping, score-wrapper input support, all-ok clean-piece behavior, and JSON-safe operator diagnostics). `tests/test_test_render_antipatterns_depth.py` pins the render-antipattern test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the detector module already produced meaningful one-path `AntiPatternResult` output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4629 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

- Recorded render-ablation depth-2 completion (frac-0102d): re-ran the full validation gate (`pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/`) on top of the merged frac-0102/0102a/0102b/0102c work and confirmed `4620 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean with no failures introduced by the new render-ablation assertions. Appended a `Depth-2 Completion` section to `sdp/notes/frac-0102a-render-ablation-depth.md` that names the locked `RenderAblationEndToEndTests` class and `test_full_pipeline_final_rendered_artifact_shape_and_content` method, cross-references the public surface (`rule_identifiers`, `filter_active_rules`, `ablate`, `build_ablation_cases`, `run_ablation_suite`, `summarize_ablation_suite`) in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/ablation.py`, marks each previously open gap as closed with the delivering task ID (`frac-0102` and `frac-0102c`), and lists the duplicate active/disabled IDs and no-rule default-renderer path as intentionally still open. Added `tests/test_frac_0102d_depth_completion.py` as a contract test pinning the new section's required fragments and at least four `- Closed:` bullets. The pre-existing `tests/test_frac_0102a_notes.py` baseline contract continues to pass unchanged. No production code, dependencies, migrations, provider secrets, database columns, runtime state directories, HTTP routes, or auth behavior were introduced; startup identity hardening anchors remain green.

- Added depth-2 render-ablation final-artifact assertion coverage (frac-0102c): `tests/test_test_render_ablation_depth.py` now requires `RenderAblationEndToEndTests.test_full_pipeline_final_rendered_artifact_shape_and_content`, and `tests/test_render_ablation.py` drives the full ablation pipeline through `rule_identifiers(...)`, `filter_active_rules(...)`, `ablate(...)`, `build_ablation_cases(...)`, `run_ablation_suite(...)`, and `summarize_ablation_suite(...)` using a deterministic structured renderer. The final suite result disables `phrase_arch` and `microtiming`, leaves only `metric_accent` active, and asserts the complete rendered artifact shape/content (`schema_version`, `score_id`, `seed_signature`, `active_rule_ids`, `sections`, `events`, and `metadata`) plus JSON round-trip behavior. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the ablation API already preserves renderer output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4620 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

